00:04:16.190 --> 00:04:19.529
This next song right here is--

00:04:19.529 --> 00:04:23.940
when I was making
this album, it was

00:04:23.940 --> 00:04:29.680
after having a bunch of meetings
and trying to figure out what

00:04:29.680 --> 00:04:31.150
I wanted to do as an artist.

00:04:31.150 --> 00:04:36.460
I feel like I got lost and
things got cluttered for me.

00:04:36.460 --> 00:04:40.190
Some of you may not know, but
I'm also in the band Maroon 5.

00:04:40.190 --> 00:04:43.780
So seeing all their success
and being a part of something

00:04:43.780 --> 00:04:50.640
so huge somewhat confused me
of who I was as a solo artist

00:04:50.640 --> 00:04:52.390
and what I wanted to say.

00:04:52.390 --> 00:04:58.810
And I decided to leave LA,
move back home to New Orleans,

00:04:58.810 --> 00:05:03.100
and really get back
down to the basis of who

00:05:03.100 --> 00:05:06.850
I felt I was and got back
to the reason I made music

00:05:06.850 --> 00:05:09.850
in the first place, which
is, at the foundation,

00:05:09.850 --> 00:05:14.020
just to do something special and
make some art that is special.

00:05:14.020 --> 00:05:15.040
I want to sell records.

00:05:15.040 --> 00:05:16.910
I want to do all
those good things.

00:05:16.910 --> 00:05:19.540
But at the basis of it, I
want to be making something

00:05:19.540 --> 00:05:21.340
that I want to make.

00:05:21.340 --> 00:05:23.130
This one's called
Claustrophobic.

00:05:27.759 --> 00:05:29.050
